The **Document categories** table lists all available categories, and displays the following columns:

**Versioning**

Indicates if versioning is enabled or disabled for the category.

**Retention**

Indicates if versioning is enabled or disabled for the category; if enabled, the configured retention period is also specified.

If no document categories have been defined yet, this section is empty. ## Creating a new document category

- Select **Document categories** on the left navigation panel.

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  **Add category** in the top-right. A new, blank document category named is created and opened in the configuration editor.

## Editing a document category
- Select **Document categories** on the left navigation panel.

- Move your mouse pointer over the row corresponding to the category that you want to edit. Click on the ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  (**More**) icon displayed on the right and select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  (**Edit**) from the list of available actions.

> Tip

You may also click on the name of the required category in the list of available **Document categories **displayed on the left navigation panel to edit it.

The category editor is opened in the configuration area; for example:

- Configure the required settings:

**Field**

**Description**

**Alias**

Name of the document category (by default: "undefined")

> Aliases for document categories must follow these rules:

- Aliases are case-sensitive.

- Aliases may contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), letters with diacritics (-, -, -), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), hyphens (-) and empty spaces ( ).

- Aliases may start with any allowed character.

- Aliases may not start or end with an empty space ( ).

- Aliases may contain at least 1 and up to 100 characters.

**Custom indexes**

Add and configure the custom indexes associated with this document category.

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Managing Indexes](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-indexes).

**System indexes**

Add and configure the system indexes associated with this document category.

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Managing Indexes](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-indexes).

**Filename index**

Select the index to use to set the name of the extracted files.

> Note

This optional configuration parameter is used to override the original filename, so that the extracted files will be 

named according to the specified index.

If empty, the original filename is used.

**Enable versioning**

Select this option to enable document versioning, and configure the following additional parameters:

- **Identifier index**: Select the index to be used as unique identifier of the document from the drop-down menu.

- **Version index**: Select the string type index to be used to store the incremental version number of a document.

> Warning

To enable document versioning both parameters must be set.

> Note

If versioning is enabled, when a document with the same value as the **Identifier index** is loaded, a new version of the document will be created, incrementing the value of the **Version index.**

**Enable retention**

Select this option to enable document retention, and configure the following additional parameter:

- **Retention period**: Number of days after which the documents in the class will be deleted.

> Note

If this option is disabled, the documents in the class will never be deleted (default setting).

> Warning

If you change the retention settings for a specific document class, the change will be applied to all documents of this class (old and new ones) during next retention job iteration (or manual launch).
